    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-30T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8441: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-30T19:00:00-06:00"
                            >May 30, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>153. Referring to first paragraph, section 2, Department’s telegram No. 72,<note
                        n="73" xml:id="d700fn73">May 29, 5 p.m., <ref target="#pg_824">p. 824</ref>;
                        reference, apparently, is to second paragraph of telegram.</note> President
                    Sacasa and General Chamorro have no knowledge of any arms coming from the United
                    States for the purposes indicated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
